Recently I was asked if I would consider being an Admin for the calender. Due to things going on in game and in real life I declined. As I have sat and thought about it I have decided that this is something that I would like to do but I have a few things that may make the admins, and the Rathe community, unwilling to have me. I thought I would just explain my situation and seek your advice. <br>
<br>
The reason I had declined the nomination was because of some changes that were going on with my guild. Basically we and a few smaller guilds were in the process of merging. The new guild, Warders of The Prophecy, is up and running. Mirth and Mayhem still exists and is being kept alive by mine and others alts so that we will have a fall back position should the merger not succeed. In this new guild I am neither a leader nor an officer and therefore will probably not be a guild representative either. <br>
<br>
When nominated by Edwina it was so that I could help be the voice of the smaller guilds. With this new merger I am no longer in a small guild but a rather large one that I am sure will be applying for access to the calender soon. <br>
<br>
Questions:<br>
<br>
* Am I still a guild rep for Mirth and Mayhem even though, for now, the guild is inactive?<br>
<br>
* Would I still be considered a good choice as an admin even though I am no longer in a small guild?<br>
<br>
I have led a guild for a year and a half. I have went through all the ups and downs and challenges that come with it. I have went from small and intimate to large and Planes capable and back to small again. I believe that I have a unique perspective that allows me to see things from all sides, small and uber. <br>
<br>
I said before that if I were an admin it would be so that I could try to help build a hamonious community here on the Rathe. I feel now that I am in a position to focus my desire and abilities on that. <br>
<br>
But the question is, will you have me?<br>
